==Address and team information==
*Address:Caixa Postal 234.
Football komplex "Estadio Varzea" [[Praia]], [[Cape Verde]].

==Jersey==
Its jersey features a striped green-white shirt with green sleeves and green socks. The uniform is identical to its fathering club, the Portuguese giants [[Sporting Clube de Portugal]].

==Stadium==
[[File:Est<U+00E1>dio da V<U+00E1>rzea.jpg|thumb|right|300px]]'''Est<U+00E1>dio da V<U+00E1>rzea''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Praia]], [[Cape Verde]].  It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches.  The stadium holds 8,000.  The stadium has seat rows in the left and right sides and a small hill and a plateau lies to the west.  The stadium is home to the three best football clubs in Cape Verde, [[Sporting Praia|Sporting]], [[CD Travadores]] and another team that plays in the first division, especially the [[Santiago, Cape Verde|Santiago]] Island first division.

==Playoff advances in history==
Sporting Clube de Praia had won a championship in 1962, later they win their first title after independence in [[1985 in sports|1985]], [[1991 in sports|1991]], [[1997 in sports|1997]], [[2002 in sports|2002]] and [[2006 in sports|2006]] beating the team known as [[Acad<U+00E9>mico do Aeroporto]] from [[Espargos, Cape Verde|Espargos]] on [[Sal, Cape Verde|Sal Island]], during the semi-finals they won the most points, six before entering the finals and lost in the first leg and won in the second leg and claimed the title for the 2005-06 season, a year later, the team claimed their second title in a row in the [[2006 in football|2006]]-[[2007 in football|07]] season and also were the championships of the island's south zone, yet again received their third title in 2007-[[2008 in football|08]] season.

Sporting Clube de Praia has been in the playoffs and reached the finals during the other times but never claimed the title, they lost to [[CS Mindelense]] 2-0 and 0-1 in the [[1988 in sports|1988]] finals, in the 2004-05 season, the team versus [[Derby FC]] was tied in the first leg, the team lost 4-3 to Derby and were the 2004-05 champions.

In the 2007/08 season, there were protests by fans over Acad<U+00E9>mica's loss on June 23 over a referee that received a penalty to one of Sporting's players.  This cause a delay in the playoffs and was finally resolved on July 8, matches resumed two days later on July 10.  The results for the first leg was 1-0 and won 3-0 against Derby in the second.

==Supporters==
The fans are known as [[Torcida]] [[Verde]] [[Santiago, Cape Verde|Santiago]]. A Torcida Verde is a cheerleader supporter of [[Sporting Clube da Praia]].The name is identical to its fathering club, the Portuguese giants Sporting Clube de Portugal.

Their[[mottos]] are: O Nosso Amor, N<U+00E3>o Conhece Dist<U+00E2>ncias-Our Love, Do not Know Distances.
Their biggest rivals are fans of [[CS Mindelense ]] called Laranja Ex<U+00E9>rcito and [[Acad<U+00E9>mica (Mindelo)]] fans called Mancha Negra.

[[Torcida]] [[Verde]] [[Santiago, Cape Verde|Santiago]] [[mascot]] is a [[lion]].

==Titles==
* '''[[Cape Verdean football Championships|Championship of Cape Verde]]''' 
** Before independence: 1961, 1969, 1974
** Since independence): 1985, 1991, 1997, 2002, 2006, 2007, 2008, 2009 

*'''[[Campeonato Regional do Santiago]]:''' 1997, 1998, 2002
*'''[[Santiago Island League (South)|Campeonato Regional do Santiago Sul]]:''' 2002, 2005, 2006, 2008
** '''Torneio Inicio:''' 2002, 2004, 2006

